<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Your link to the Net
 &HT;    By Staff Reports
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _
</P>
<P>
   www.adcritic.com _ Got a favorite commercial? You can probably
find it here, where the best ads on TV are downloadable. Featuring
everything from the ``Wazzzup!'' ads to the latest movie trailers,
you'll find it all in easily digestible words from the sponsors.
</P>
<P>
   www.hcs.harvard.edu/(tilde)igp/glass.html _ The ``I Can Eat
Glass Project,'' isn't what it sounds like. What it is, rather, is
a site where the creator is compiling a list of ways to say, ``I
can eat glass, it doesn't hurt me'' in various languages. Smart?
According to the site, it's being used as a teaching tool at the
University of Texas.
</P>
<P>
   www.fametracker.com _ Describing itself as the ``Farmer's
Almanac of Celebrity Worth,'' this Canadian site (from the creators
of ``Hissyfit'' and ``Mightybigtv.com'') mercilessly skewers
celebrities who deserve it and celebrates under-the-radar
performers who need the attention. Smart, snarky and endlessly
readable, it's like having an evil, gossipy friend.
</P>
<P>
   www.PeaceForAll.com _ Yes, it's true _ you can make the Web a
better place. Peaceforall.com allows you to donate for free to the
U.S. Association for the UN High Commissioner for Refugees. By
clicking on a button, you provide a small, but meaningful donation.
This site and www.EndCancer Now.com are inspired by TheHunger
Site.com.
</P>
<P>
   www.peanutpress.com _ Ever since Stephen King's ``Riding the
Bullet'' sold like a bullet, e-books are finally coming into their
own as a viable way to read your favorites. Peanutpress.com's books
are made for personal digitial assistants like Palm Pilots or PDAs
running Windows CE. Portable and readable entertainment.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
