you into four-letter trouble. ``No.'' No matter what Nancy Reagan
would tell you, it's hard to just say no in the workplace. Bosses
demand long hours, clients push for constant service, colleagues
beg for help. And if you give in to all their requests, your spouse
just might head for the door. By DAVE MURPHY.
</P>
<P>
   MOTLEY-FOOLS (San Francisco) _ One of my favorite Web sites is
the Motley Fool (fool.com), because it approaches personal finance
the same way workers should approach their jobs. Here are a few
Foolish lessons, for your money and your life. By DAVE MURPHY.
