<SLUG> BC-CHEFSSECRETS-SF </SLUG>
 CHRON  
 Cooks Have a New Source for Chefs' Secrets  &HT;       
 By Miriam Morgan  
 c. 1999 The San Francisco Chronicle  
<TEXT>
 &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; SAN FRANCISCO _  &LR; For several months, The Chronicle's weekly Secrets
of Success column has told Food section readers how to replicate
some of Bay Area's best restaurant dishes. Now, the recipes _ and
the secrets behind them _ are all in one place: ``The Secrets of
Success Cookbook,'' by Chronicle food editor and restaurant critic
Michael Bauer.
<P>
   The book includes more than 200 recipes, each accompanied by the
chef's tricks or tips. Those little hints _ ranging from how to
choose, salt and prepare the meat for Zuni Cafe's hamburger, rated
the best in town, to how to brown the sugar for the Grand Cafe's
signature Banana Cream Tart _ not only distinguish the recipe but
let the home cook in on how some of the country's best food is
created.
</P>
<P>
   The recipes, which go from breakfast to cocktails, desserts and
everything in between, have been thoroughly tested for home use _ a
huge plus since chef's recipes can sometimes be minefields for all
but the most experienced professional.
</P>
<P>
   Like the columns, each recipe also comes with descriptions of
the restaurant and chef _ sort of abbreviated restaurant reviews.
And the index includes basic information about each restaurant for
those who want to dine at the source.
</P>
<P>
   Publishers Weekly calls the book ``the ultimate tour of the Bay
Area restaurant scene,'' with ``clearly written'' recipes perfect
for ``those who enjoy cooking and want to better understand the
process _ without investing a lifetime in the kitchen.''
</P>
<P>
   But don't put away your clipping scissors just yet. Although
several of the recipes in the book have already appeared in The
Chronicle, the weekly Food section column features restaurants that
weren't open when the recipes were compiled, as well as new dishes
created by up-and-coming and well-established chefs.
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  ``The Secrets of Success Cookbook: Signature Recipes and &LR; 
 &LR; Insider Tips From San Francisco's Best Restaurants,'' by &LR;   &LR; Michael
Bauer (Chronicle Books, 384 pages softcover, $19.95). &LR;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-04-12-00 1257EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
