SAN FRANCISCO _  SOURCEOYSTER  _ As animals go, oysters seem rather
placid. Actually, says Michael Watchorn, co-owner of Hog Island
Oyster Co., they are competitive creatures. If if you don't
separate the fast growers from the slow ones, the little guys will
be starved out by their voracious bigger brethren. He should know.
Watchorn has been growing oysters for nearly 20 years. 
 By Karola Saekel  
 c. 1999 The San Francisco Chronicle    
