SAN FRANCISCO _  &UR; POTPOURRI &LR;  _ Many older observant Jews remember
the days of sweet kosher wines that tasted like Concord grape juice
with alcohol. With the '90s, the character and style of kosher wine
began to change, as Passover meals and celebrations of other Jewish
holidays, called for dry varietal wines with all the class and
character of nonkosher wines.
</P>
<P>
   The misconception is that kosher means inferior. Today's kosher
winemakers want you to know that is not true. &QL; 
