<HEADER>
A4675 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r d BC-RAINYDAY-RECIPE-TEX     04-12 0299
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-RAINYDAY-RECIPE-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
COMFORT FOOD FOR A RAINY DAY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   If April showers will indeed fall, here's a great recipe for a
rainy day. It's a good way to pull the kids away from TV for a
while, and it's an instructive activity that guarantees fun with
instant results.
</P>
<P>
   The recipe, inspired by Chinese and other Asian cooking, comes
from chef Clark McDaniel of Fort Worth's Angeluna restaurant. He
says you can use nearly anything for filling, from chopped wieners
to browned and drained ground beef.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   STEAMED BUNS
</P>
<P>
   Makes 8 servings
</P>
<P>
   2 cans Hungry Jack biscuits
</P>
<P>
   1 egg, beaten
</P>
<P>
   2 to 3 tablespoons water
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon sesame seeds
</P>
<P>
   2 to 3 tablespoons flour
</P>
<P>
   2 cups cooked chicken, shredded
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup diced mushrooms
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup diced water chestnuts
</P>
<P>
   1 to 2 teaspoons olive oil
</P>
<P>
   4 tablespoons hoisin sauce
</P>
<P>
   Make filling first by sauteeing mushrooms and water chestnuts in
a dash of olive oil, mixing in shredded chicken. Remove from heat
and add enough hoisin sauce to bind. Chill mixture. Meanwhile,
prepare buns by flouring a work surface and rolling out biscuit
dough. On each biscuit, leave a small, dime-sized spot in center
unrolled. Put a small amount of the chilled filling in the center
of four biscuits; brush edges with a wash made from beaten egg and
a little water. Put a plain, rolled biscuit atop each biscuit with
filling, pleat edges until closed. Brush each bun with egg wash,
then dust with sesame seeds. Steam in a boiling steamer for 10
minutes. Serve, if desired, with a little hoisin sauce that has
been thinned with chicken stock.
</P>
<P>
   _June Naylor Rodriguez
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
</TEXT>
