or coming up with unique approaches to solving problems. Try to
make sure that when your boss thinks of you, a particular strength
is the first thing to pop into her mind.
</P>
<P>
   _ You need a touch of arrogance.
</P>
<P>
   Anybody recommending individual stocks has to have a huge amount
of confidence. After all, thousands of people recommend stocks, and
not all of them can be right, even in a bull market. If you don't
have enough arrogance to stick to your beliefs when others
challenge you, you won't last long.
</P>
<P>
   Few answers in the working world are absolutely right or
absolutely wrong, and sometimes you have to be arrogant enough to
