Without a little of that arrogance, you'll never challenge yourself
as much as you should.
</P>
<P>
   _ Don't rely too much on any one source.
</P>
<P>
   Although I like the Motley Fool, you'd be nuts to take what
anyone says as the gospel without doing your own research. That's
why I'll always check out stocks at places like Yahoo
(quote.yahoo.com), CNET (news.com) or MSN Money Central
(moneycentral.msn.com).
</P>
<P>
   Even if you're with a great company, resist the temptation to
rely on it for everything, such as when all your friends are
co-workers and all your money is tied up in the company's stock.
