him of such enduring interest? His work has never gone out of
print. And now a new generation of readers seems to have discovered
him all over again. By Dinitia Smith.
</P>
<P>
   NAZI-ART-MUSEUMS (New York) _ The Museum of Modern Art, the
etropolitan Museum and other big art institutions will list their
Nazi-era acquisitions on the Internet. By Judith H. Dobrzynski.
</P>
<P>
   LOUVRE-WORLD-ART (Paris) _ Four newly renovated galleries of the
Louvre dedicated exclusively to art from Africa, Asia, Oceania and
the Americas will open this week. From now on, the 112 works of art
on display there will be treated as the aesthetic equals of, say,
the Egyptian, Greek or Renaissance art elsewhere in the vast
building. By Alan Riding.
</P>
