<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-20MINUTE-MENUS-ADV26-NYTSF </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
$ADV26 
 HEALTHY 20-MINUTE MENUS: SAUTEED CHICKEN AND FENNEL, ROASTED
POTATOES  
 (FOR RELEASE WED., APRIL 26, 2000, AND THEREAFTER)
</HEADLINE>
   ATTENTION EDITORS: The following material from The New York Times
Syndicate is for use by 20-MINUTE-MENUS clients. Nonsubscribers can
use this article only by special arrangement. For purchase
information, see end of text. 
 By MARIAN BURROS    
 c.2000 Foxcraft Ltd.    
<TEXT>
<P>
   You will find nothing unusual about this menu until you come to
the ingredient in the chicken recipe, garam masala. Before you
discard the menu because you don't have the seasoning in the house
_ whatever it may be _ please read on.
</P>
<P>
   Garam masala is an Indian spice blend that contains coriander,
cinnamon, cloves, cardamom, mace and black peppercorns. All of
those ingredients are available in most ordinary supermarkets. They
do not produce a hot seasoning, but rather one that is subtly sweet
and full of aroma.
</P>
<P>
   If you cannot find garam masala easily, you can make your own by
combining: 1 2/3 tablespoons ground coriander seeds, 3/4 teaspoon
cinnamon, 3/4 tablespoon ground cumin, 3/4 teaspoon ground
cardamom, 3/4 tablespoon mace and 3/4 tablespoon ground pepper.
Stir well and store whatever is leftover in a tightly covered
container.
</P>
<P>
   When using the mixture in this recipe sprinkle the chicken
lightly on both sides with it, something more than a teaspoon but
less than a tablespoon.
</P>
<P>
   In the chicken recipe cooking the fennel for a long time makes
it as sweet as the cooked onions but with that wonderful mild
licorice taste. The tomato paste adds a touch of acidity and the
whole is a fine balance of flavors.
</P>
<P>
   The potatoes could not be simpler and proof that you can have
crisp slices without deep fat frying. There are a lot of
vegetables, like sweet potatoes, zucchini, yellow squash that can
be roasted the same way.
</P>
<P>
   SAUTEED CHICKEN AND FENNEL
</P>
<P>
   2 medium-large heads of fennel
</P>
<P>
   Olive oil spray
</P>
<P>
   8 ounces whole onion or 7 ounces chopped, ready-cut (1 2/3 cups)
</P>
<P>
   12 ounces skinless boneless chicken breasts
</P>
<P>
   Garam masala to sprinkle over breasts
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup no-salt-added chicken stock or water
</P>
<P>
   2 teaspoons tomato paste
</P>
<P>
   Few sprigs fresh oregano to yield 1 tablespoon chopped
</P>
<P>
   Freshly ground black pepper to taste
</P>
<P>
   1. Wash and remove tough outer stalk of fennel; cut off tops and
trim the bottom. Cut the fennel lengthwise in quarters.
</P>
<P>
   2. Heat nonstick pan large enough to hold all the ingredients
until it is very hot; reduce heat to medium and spray generously
with olive oil spray. Add the fennel and saute until the fennel
begins to brown.
</P>
<P>
   3. Meanwhile, chop onion and add to fennel. Continue cooking
until onion begins to take on color.
</P>
<P>
   4. Meanwhile wash, dry and cut chicken into strips, then cut
each strip in half; sprinkle with garam masala; add to fennel and
onion and continue cooking until the chicken lightly brown, just a
few minutes.
</P>
<P>
   5. Wash and chop oregano and add with water and tomato paste;
cover, reduce heat to low and cook until chicken is done. Season
with pepper. Sprinkle with parsley.
</P>
<P>
   Yield 2 servings
</P>
<P>
   ROASTED POTATOES
</P>
<P>
   12 ounces large new potatoes, sliced 1/8 inch thick
</P>
<P>
   Olive oil spray
</P>
<P>
   Salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste.
</P>
<P>
   1. Turn oven to 450 degrees.
</P>
<P>
   2. Scrub potatoes (do not peel) and slice 1/8 inch thick by hand
or using food processor.
</P>
<P>
   3. Spray large baking sheet with pan spray. Arrange potato
slices in single layer on baking sheet and spray them on top.
Season with salt and pepper and place in bottom third of oven and
roast until the potatoes begin to brown on top; turn and continue
baking, about 10 minutes total.
</P>
<P>
   Yield: 2 servings
</P>
<P>
   GAME PLAN
</P>
<P>
   Turn on oven and prepare potatoes through step 3.
</P>
<P>
   Prepare chicken through step 3.
</P>
<P>
   Turn potatoes.
</P>
<P>
   Finish chicken.
</P>
<P>
   YOUR PANTRY
</P>
<P>
   Olive oil pan spray
</P>
<P>
   Onion
</P>
<P>
   Tomato paste
</P>
<P>
   Whole black pepper
</P>
<P>
   Salt
</P>
<P>
   SHOPPING LIST
</P>
<P>
   2 medium-large heads fennel
</P>
<P>
   12 ounces skinless boneless chicken breasts
</P>
<P>
   Jar garam masala
</P>
<P>
   Small container no-salt-added chicken stock
</P>
<P>
   Bunch fresh oregano
</P>
<P>
   12 ounces large new potatoes
</P>
<P>
   Nutrition Information per serving: 580 calories, 6 grams fat,
105 milligrams cholesterol, 365 milligrams sodium, 50 grams
protein, 85 grams carbohydrate.
</P>
<P>
   Questions may be sent to Marian Burros by electronic mail. Her
address is: marbur(at)nytimes.com. The (at) represents the symbol
on your keyboard. Please include your name and daytime telephone
number. Questions of general interest will be answered in this
column. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ------------------------------------------------- &QC;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; EDITOR: Visit The New York Times Syndicate Web site at
http://www.nytimes.com/syndicate for more information on
20MINUTE-MENUS and other features. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NONSUBSCRIBERS: To publish a ``separate-buy'' feature article, it
must be purchased. Please contact one of these sales
representatives: &LR;
</P>
<P>
   --U.S. and Canada: DEBRA WEYDERT in New Jersey at
1-732-390-4480; fax, 732-390-4697.
</P>
<P>
   --Europe and Asia: KARL HORWITZ in Paris at 47-42-17-11; fax,
47-42-80-44 or 47-42-18-81; telex, 282-942.
</P>
<P>
   --Latin America: ANA PENA in New York, 212-499-3333; fax,
212-499-3382. &QL;
</P>
