<P>
   SCI-ONEILL-DEATH (Undated) _ Eugene O'Neill, playwright of souls
in search of forgiveness, was given an absolution of sorts himself,
in the pages of a medical journal. Contrary to O'Neill's own
suspicion that heavy drinking in his youth caused the brain disease
that crippled him later in life, a new report confirms that he died
of a rare brain disorder, but says alcohol was not to blame. Far
more likely, the progressive deterioration of O'Neill's brain was
due to a rare genetic disorder, said Dr. Bruce H. Price, chairman
of the neurology department at McLean Hospital in Boston, and
coauthor of an article in the New England Journal of Medicine. By
Denise Grady.
</P>
