<P>
   DRAFT-RISKYPICKS _ During the NFL annual meeting last month in
Palm Beach, the owners and head coaches held a two-hour discussion
of how to combat the off-the-field problems. At one point, Denver's
Pat Bowlen stood up and gave his recommendation. ``We've got to
stop taking these guys,'' he said. Will Bowlen's peers listen to
him? There is a long list of college football players who were
arrested during the past year and charged with an assortment of
offenses. NFL teams, if they are serious in their attempt to weed
out potential problem players, must decide how heavily to weigh
each incident. And many observers believe when the teams are faced
with the moment of decision _ the clock ticking as NFL commissioner
Paul Tagliabue stands at the podium, ready to announce their pick
on-the-field potential will count for more than potential
off-the-field problems. (Woods, Palm Beach Post). WITH CHART of
this year's risk picks.
</P>
