<P>
   Here are the stories New York Times editors are planning for
Thursday, April 13 Page 1. The NYT frontpage advisory, with layout
description, will move by 7:30 p.m. ET. The NYT News Service Night
Supervisor is Pat Ryan (888-346-9867).
</P>
<P>
   PERU-ELECT (Lima, Peru) _ Tension mounts as people still await
final election results, which government said would come Wednesday,
to decide whether Alberto Fujimori, the president, will be forced
to a second-round election. By Clifford Krauss.
</P>
<P>
   CUBAN-BOY _ Developments. With resolution of his fate drawing
nearer, Elian Gonzalez on Wednesday moved to a sympathetic nun's
house as Attorney General Janet Reno traveled to Miami to try to
settle the custody dispute over the young Cuban refugee. Reno left
Washington in the afternoon to meet with the Miami relatives who
have cared for Elian since he was found floating in the Atlantic
off Florida at Thanksgiving. Reporting by Rick Bragg in Miami and
David Johnston in Washington.
</P>
