<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SHOPPING-GUIDE13-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Locate hard to find items
 &HT;    By Marylin Johnson
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Having trouble finding a particular item? We'll try to help you
locate it. But because of the volume of mail, we cannot track down
every request. Readers whose queries are answered in the column
will receive a blue-and-cream canvas Buyer's Edge tote bag. Write
us at Buyer's Edge Find It,The Atlanta Journal-Constitution, P.O.
Box 4689, Atlanta, GA 30302; e-mail us at buyersedge(at)ajc.com
(please include your name, the city you live in and daytime phone
number); or call 404-582-7642.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Could you find earring replacement backs? I used to find them
at beauty superstores, but no longer.
</P>
<P>
   _Sharon Hart, Atlanta
</P>
<P>
   A: Our back was to the wall, but we managed to find these
replacement earring backs at Michaels Arts and Crafts, at the
location in Mall Corners Shopping Center, 2131 Pleasant Hill Road,
Suite 200, Duluth (770-813-8328). Crafting Expressions makes a
variety of backs ($2.99 a package) including stainless steel or
gold butterfly styles as well as silver-and-plastic or
gold-and-plastic backs.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Where in metro Atlanta can I find Mr. Muscle? It is a very
good cleaner on stoves and grills. A friend of mine found it in
Memphis.
</P>
<P>
   _Addie Harkness, Decatur, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: After a bit of searching, we flexed our muscles and came up
with Mr. Muscle, the oven and grill cleaner, at Atlanta Fixture &AMP;
Sales Co., 3185 Northeast Expressway, Chamblee (770-455-8844). A
19-ounce can is $3.98. Made by Drackett, a division of S.C.
Johnson, this cleaner is designed to work on cold surfaces. It
should not be used on continuous-clean or self-cleaning ovens, nor
should you let the product come in contact with floor coverings,
linoleum, copper, chrome, plastics or painted surfaces.
</P>
<P>
   Q: When stores advertise furniture, they very often show
artificial fruit on tables. It's a pretty, decorative touch, and I
would like to buy some apples and lemons, but so far, I can't find
any. Can you help?
</P>
<P>
   _Nancy
</P>
<P>
   Robinson,
</P>
<P>
   Atlanta
</P>
<P>
   A: Now, your fruit will never go bad or be out of season. We
picked up our artificial fruit at Garden Ridge, 1887 Willow Trail
in Norcross (770-921-1833). In our 10-inch fruit bowl ($1.97) are
shiny red apples (88 cents each), a Golden Delicious apple ($1.98),
lemons (88 cents each), a large pear ($2.98) and frosted grapes
($3.88 a bunch).
</P>
<P>
   Q: I am trying to find beignets, the little French doughnuts. We
had a little place here in Decatur that served them, but it went
out of business.
</P>
<P>
   _Ann Villwolk, Decatur, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: Beignets make a yummy treat, especially when served with cafe
au lait. The Cafe du Monde coffee stand in New Orleans has been
serving these tasty treats since 1862. A branch of the famous Cafe
du Monde is located at Underground Atlanta, 110 Lower Alabama St.
S.W. (404-681-2719). Three beignets are $1.45. There you can also
buy the beignet mix (28-ounce box, $2.75) and make your French
doughnuts at home. If you want to order the beignet mix via mail,
call 1-800-772-2927. Or visit the Web site at www.cafedumonde.com.
</P>
<P>
   Huey's, 1816 Peachtree St. N.W. (404-873-2037) also serves a
version of beignets. According to a spokesman, theirs are ``lighter
and fried in peanut oil.'' Three square beignets are $3.50.
</P>
<P>
   Q: About a year ago, I received a sample of a moisturizer for
oily skin from L'Oreal called ``Matify.'' It was an excellent
product, but I have not been able to find it in any store. Does the
company still make it?
</P>
<P>
   _Deborah Wilbanks, Gainesville, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: Unfortunately, L'Oreal no longer makes this particular
product. However, the company has come out with a replacement:
HydraFresh Moisturizer for oily skin (about $9). The moisturizer,
which is absorbed in a flash, is part of a skin-care regimen that
also contains a cleanser and toner (each about $5). It is available
at chain drugstores and mass market retailers.
</P>
<P>
   Q: My family and I use Coast bath soap in the yellow wrapper.
Procter &AMP; Gamble says it doesn't make it anymore. I wondered if
anybody has a stock of it so we can buy it up.
</P>
<P>
   _Ed Woolbright, Roswell, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: You are right. Procter &AMP; Gamble did discontinue the Sunspray
Scent of Coast soap in November. However, we stumbled on a cache at
Ingles Supermarket, 4815 Rockbridge Road, Stone Mountain
(404-299-0698) A pack of three bars of the deodorant soap is $1.89.
</P>
<P>
   _Contributing: Michelle C. Brooks
</P>
<P>
   Marylin Johnson writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
