Olympic hopeful named Lori Munz was badly injured in an auto
accident near Sydney. Two weeks later, she returned to the pool
with her shattered right leg in a brace and did a few cautious
laps. It was an inspirational story _ so inspirational, in fact,
that when Munz returned to the pool, she already had signed
exclusive agreements to tell her tale to an Australian TV network
and a newspaper. Such is the disturbing state of sports today....By
Christopher Clarey, The International Herald Tribune (4-11) &QL;
