<P>
   &UR; BLACK SHEEP OF LIBYA EDGES BACK INTO FOLD &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; GADDAFI-MENDS-FENCES-INDEPENDENT &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   You tell the French president to his face that he's a hypocrite.
You urge the Italian prime minister to boot the U.S. Sixth Fleet
out of Naples. You accuse Europeans of regarding Africans as
``gorillas.'' Not, it might seem, the best way for one of the
blackest of international black sheep to set about returning to the
fold. But then, Colonel Muammar Gaddafi was never one to play by
the rules. Libya is starting to mend fences with the world, but in
typically idiosyncratic fashion....By Rupert Cornwell, The
Independent of London (4-12) &QL;
