<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    With OSCILLATE. For release Sunday, April 16.
 &HT;    c.2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   LA NINA PLUS NPO-2 EQUALS MORE BIG HURRICANES
</P>
<P>
   An analysis by University of Missouri-Columbia climatologists
suggests that when NPO-2 phases coincide with La Nina years,
``big'' Category 3, 4, and 5 hurricanes are more frequent by
roughly one per year than during La Nina years that correspond with
NPO-1 phases.
</P>
<P>
   Storms per year.......62-year
average.........NPO-1..........NPO-2
</P>
<P>
   During La Ninas..........2.7......................... 2.0
..............2.9
</P>
<P>
   During El Ninos...........1.7..........................0.8
..............2.0
</P>
